From: Kamil Lulko <limakzagan@gmail.com>
Subject: opengl32: handle Adreno-style "OpenGL ES X.Y" version strings

Wine's parse_gl_version assumes the version string starts with the major
version digit ("3.2.0" desktop GL) and ERRs out otherwise. Android's
Adreno Vulkan driver, when wine probes the GL string via wined3d/winex11
fallback, returns:

    "OpenGL ES 3.2 V@0762.41 (GIT@…) (Date:09/19/25)"

— the leading "OpenGL ES " prefix makes atoi() return 0 and wine logs:

    err:opengl:parse_gl_version Invalid OpenGL major version 0.
    err:opengl:parse_gl_version Invalid OpenGL version string …

Skip a leading non-digit prefix so the parser lands on the actual version
digits regardless of vendor prefix. Affects D3D11→wined3d→OpenGL fallback
path for plugins that try GL when DXVK D3D11 device creation fails
(observed with IK Multimedia AmpliTube 5 on Android + Adreno).

diff --git a/dlls/opengl32/unix_wgl.c b/dlls/opengl32/unix_wgl.c
--- a/dlls/opengl32/unix_wgl.c
+++ b/dlls/opengl32/unix_wgl.c
@@ -445,6 +445,11 @@
 static const char *parse_gl_version( const char *gl_version, int *major, int *minor )
 {
     const char *ptr = gl_version;
+    /* Skip a leading non-digit prefix (e.g. "OpenGL ES " on Adreno) so the
+     * parser lands on the actual version digits. Desktop GL strings start
+     * with the major version directly; mobile/ES drivers prepend their
+     * name. */
+    while (*ptr && !isdigit( *ptr )) ++ptr;

     *major = atoi( ptr );
     if (*major <= 0)
